This year , women have won the Nobel Prize in Physics in all fields
A record five women now in Stockholm took the hands of the Swedish King Carl XVI Gustaf of this year's Nobel Prize in technical categories and for literature.
In addition to the four scientists between them was a German writer Herta M. of Romanian origin.
The Nobel Prize in medicine have received two American Elizabeth Blackburn and Carol Greiderová together with their fellow Dutchman Jack Szostakem for research in the field of chromosomes .
She received the award for chemistry Izraelka Ada Jonathová, together with the Americans Venkatramanem Ramakrishnanem and Thomas Steitzem for clarification of the structure and function of ribozomů.
The last laureátku was the Nobel Prize for economics, which received the American Elinor Ostromová and her fellow countryman Oliver Williamson for analysis of economic governance.
The only technical categories, which this year has passed off without držitelky, was a physics.
This award today scientists carried Charles Kao for research in the field of optical fibres and George Smith with Willardem Boylem for the invention of CCD chip, which is the basis of all digital cameras, faxes or astronomical telescopes.
Each winning took a diploma, the Nobel medal and a certificate of earnings financial rewards.
The amounts for each category of ten million Swedish crowns (about 25 million CZK).
