Experts have also have clear in the procedure for vaccination.
The new vaccination
The vaccine free of charge for children in August
From January may be free vaccination against pneumococcal children who were born last year 2nd August and later.
The only condition is that he still does not even one dose of the vaccine.
Who began to vaccinate last year or earlier, he must pay for himself and other booster vaccination.
The first dose of vaccine should be made between 3 and 5 month the age of the child.
Last year, voluntarily left their children vaccinated against pneumokokům a quarter of families.
Parents yet paid 1600 crowns for one dose and more.
The vaccination of the youngest children are the need for four doses.
Overall, experts estimate that health insurance companies to get on the vaccine dose of 300 to 450 thousand crowns a year.
Saves but treatment that children without vaccination needed.
Not worth all the area vaccination of children gave about 500 thousand a year.
Reimbursements vaccination was introduced so-called Janotovým package.
The pneumococcus causes inflammation of the middle ear, but also serious infections including brain fever and blood poisoning.
The pneumococcal infection in our country per year die in hospitals under investigation to 28 children under 10 years.
In addition to the Czech Republic introduced by the vaccination of children against pneumococci around in 40 countries.
The vaccination will be mandatory?
At the same time but there are views that the future could be the vaccination mandatory.
From January to be paid by insurance companies and optional.
It would be better to vaccination, indicated as the head of the civic association Unmute Rudolf Kalovský.
His association pneumococcal vaccine in the long run .
Experts at the international conference that our association took part, were not entirely satisfied with the fact that we have a voluntary vaccination.
It's not exactly ideal.
On the other hand, we are glad that we have managed to push through at least this.
I think that's the road that now we have to step in, said Kalovský.
The Ministry of Health but the vaccination against pneumokokům wants to change.
At this moment about it at all, said his spokesperson Vlastimil hornet.
