Mr. Ellis draws from the works of other writers and historians and often returns to the threat that the hunters threatens the survival of the species.
Even if hunting is banned in Norway, America and Russia, the killing continues in Greenland and Canada, where hunting from helicopters and Indians jumping and all are armed with assault rifles executive, which blasting their prey.
The irony is that it takes place in the water to the north of these two fishing nations and that ice will eventually be the largest.
In his new book "The Ice" Alun Anderson, former editor of New Scientist, has a clear responsibility of the dismal science in the Arctic and interesting glimpse of how it can change the future.
Not at all, researchers are answers.
Neither the meteorology and oceánografové do not have an adequate response to the speed of change.
This lack of testing.
The research trip Fridtjofa Nansena at the end of the 19th and early 20th century for the first time, indicated that there is a movement of floating ice.
Submarines in the Cold War, then shifting the mapping watersheds when podplouvaly.
Satellite survey and extensive field probes floating glaciers are a useful supplement, but many are still held by brave individuals tábořícím in winter.
Mr. Anderson peering into an extremely fragile world Company systémuu ¨ inside the Arctic ice, create stékáním salt water, which can be found in the freezing point contracts.
But since výse that bear the microscopic wonders uvnitž, it is doomed to extinction, as soon as he moves summer ice, which take place sometime between 2013 and 2050.
