Concerns about safety, highlighted by massive coordinated bomb attacks on Tuesday, and political instability, as well as the withdrawal of the U.S. military is likely to discourage U.S. companies from more intensive business activities in Iraq, which has the third largest proven reserves of raw materials, analysts say.
