In an ageing China, change course
Weijia Wang and her husband grew up surrounded by propaganda posters, on which read that "Mother Earth is too tired to fund more children" and "One child also means a grave also.
Then they got a lesson that when the official government in Shanghai, alarmována low birth rate and ageing of the population in their city, suddenly changed course in this summer and began to encourage young couples, their response was immediate and determined: never.
We have always spent all their time and energy just one child.
We have nothing left for the second, says Wang, 31 years, the human resources, which has 8měsíčního son.
More than 30 years of China's policy of having only one child has been introduced and thus created two generations, only the notoriously boubelatých and zhýčkaných children affectedly dubbed "little emperors", threatening the country's population crisis.
The average fertility rate decreased to 1.8 children per couple in comparison with six than vpolitika vsoupila into force , according to the UN .
The distribution of the population, where the number of residents aged 60 and above, predicts that the 12-year-old will grow from 16.7 percent of the population in 2020 to 31,1 percent in 2050. That's far above the average of around 20 percent.
An imbalance is more affluent coastal cities with a population with higher education, for example in Shanghai.
Last year, people at the age of 60 years of age and above accounted for almost 22 percent in Shanghai registered population, while the birth rate was less than one child per couple.
Xie Lingli, director of the Shanghai municipal committee on population and family planning said, many couples have children, "to help reduce the proportion of aging population and reduce the numerical status of the workforce in the future."
He says it's about "being old, it does not mean to be rich - as in developed countries such as Japan or Sweden.
The gradual
As has been inserted into the constitution of the country in 1978, China's one child policy is probably still the most controversial mandate, established under the rule of the Communist Party.
The pair, who violated the policy, face enormous fines - up to three times their annual salary in some areas - and discrimination at work.
China's official places are advocating policies that helped the country avoid critical of natural resources, while human rights advocates were condemned to enforce the policy.
In rural areas, some officials forcing pregnant women in the second child to undergo abortions.
In addition, many couples had to undergo sexisticky selective abortion, leading to an unnaturally high proportion of men against women.
In recent years, population officials were progressively less severe in its opinion on the one-child policy.
In 2004, as a rule permit výce exceptions - including city dwellers, members of ethnic minorities and in cases where a man and woman were only child - and in 2007 to mitigate the diction of their passwords, promote a hard line.
Qiao Xiaochun, a professor at the Beijing Institute of population research universities, said that officials of the central government has previously debated the more radical changes, such as allowing couples to have two children if one of the partners was an only child.
In June, the Šanghai became the first Chinese city, which launched an aggressive campaign for incitement to more at.
Almost overnight, the posters urge parents to have only one child, replaced with copies thereof, describing in detail how it would be legitimate to have a second child and how to apply for permission.
The city administration has sent officials to plan families and volunteers, so that they can meet with couples in their houses and vsouvali leaflets under doors.
Also promised to provide emotional and financial counseling for those who have decided to have more than one child.
The reaction was cool, said officials for planning families.
Zarmucující response
Although officials in a rural town near Shanghai experienced an increase in the interest of couples who would like to have a second child after the start of the campaign, most urban precincts were reported changes.
Huinan urban district with a population of 115000, for example, still registered four to five cases per month.
Frustrated officials in Shanghai said that despite the campaign is the number of births in 2010 is still expected to only about 165,000 - slightly higher than in 2009 but lower than in 2008.
Juying Feng, head of the committee for family planning in Shanghai čtvti Caol said that financial considerations were probably the main reason why people do not want to have more children.
They want to provide the best first child, he said.
Yang Jiawei, 27 years old, and his wife, Liu Juanjuan, 26 years, she said she would like to have two children and they are legally allowed to be.
But like many Chinese, who have only a lack of health and life insurance, provided by the government.
Without dociální reception network could be the choice of irresponsible.
People in the west on a one-child policy is wrong as a matter of legal question, says Yang, a structural engineer, whose wife is in her seventh month of pregnancy in volume with the first child.
Yes, we have been deprived of the chance to have more than one child.
But the problem is not only in politics.
It is about money.
Other couples show the psychological reasons for hesitation.
Wang, manager of human resources, says that they want only one child, because she also was an only child: "We focus our families and all of us cared.
We were not used for the provision of care and in fact we did not want to worry about others.
Chen Zijian, 42 years old, who vlatní translation company, has put much nepokrytěji.
For dvoukariérové parents of the middle class, who reduced fertility rates, he said, be successful means to be selfish.
Today's 20 and 30letí waxing consult on their parents as in the first days číského probíjející experiment with capitalism and do not want this way of živita for myself, he says.
Just one child places enormous demands on time parents, he says.
The mother must sacrifice for at least two years of my social life.
Then there are issues propstoru - “you have to rebuild your apartment ” - and the strategy -“ you must have a summary prepared at the time when the child 9 months for a good pre-school education.
Most of his friends wants to be content with one child, says Che, but not with two.
