We don't want to make too many victims.
UN group has outlined a plan to reduce emissions.
The UN sponsored conference on climate change -- with a large neukázněnými position and mutual osočováním -- is once again on Friday focused on the release of the document, which proposes ambitious cuts in the amount of greenhouse gases over the next 40 years with industrialised nations, bearing most of the burden in the immediate term.
The text , which may provide the basis for a final political agreement on the regulation of greenhouse gases , stresses the remaining obstacles , as well as the way forward .
But it was seen important progress in the negotiations which took place at the wrong time with more than 100 world leaders who come to Copenhagen next week.
UN Working Group created an ad hoc, the text subtly indicates how much money rich countries should give those poor to cope with global warming in the short term and long term.
And provides a whole range of choices for the key issues, including how to develop and manage emerging economies in order to reduce their output of carbon and what should be the upper limit for the increase in global temperature, which will be political leaders still able to tolerate.
This dodábá process a great deal of flexibility, says John Coequyt, Senior Washington Representative of Sierra Club.
Michael Zammit Cutajar, who suggested šestistránkový document zestručnění from 180 pages of text from the meeting to focus on what a top official on the issue at the UN climate change, Yvo de Boer, described as a "big picture".
The outlines of a possible settlement, in which he could be jointly industrial nations to reduce their emissions by 25 to 45 percent compared with 1990 levels, while the main developing countries could reduce their emissions during this period for 15 to 30 percent.
Together, the country to reduce emissions by 2050 between 50 and 95 per cent.
