The first British train with a speed of 140 miles per hour this Monday feelings
In 5: 13 Monday morning whistle cut through the darkness on the departure of the train, which meant the revolution transport in Britain.
The first high-speed passenger train in the country reaches a speed of 140 miles per hour and fly from Ashford in Kent to London St Pancras and beyond the distance of 58 miles in 38 minutes.
