One track should lead to Scotland.
"It seems there has been the most effective choice," he said, and a judge of the railways.
Once that is done, journey times between London and Edinburkem shall be reduced to two hours and 40 minutes.
The first stage, which will not be open before the year 2025, it could enable passengers to travel between London and Birmingham in 49 minutes compared with more than one hour in the present.
Proposals should enable trains to travel at a speed of 2 250 miles per hour, which would have made of the British network, the fastest in Europe.
The initial line already proposes to hold the trains in the length of 400 m , which would have been able to carry the 1100 .
Up to 18 sets could operate every hour on the route London - Birmingham.
This means that the London terminal would be able to serve the needs of up to 20 000 passengers per hour.
Due to capital constraints, it is expected that the existing stations would be extended so that pojmula high-speed network.
Experts from železničníhoprůmyslu argues that only San Pancras International and Euston offer such potential.
Lord Adonis will announce whether is or is not going to implement this scheme, but an extensive public consultation and planning procedures mean that keč a final decision will not be forthcoming before the general election.
Even if the wheels in motion, the network should build in instalments.
Trains should be first placed into service, not on the high-speed lines, but the existing routes north of Birmingham and maintain the journey times between London and Scotland over three hours.
This is regarded as a crucial point of contact for the transition from the aircraft on the trains , a reference point for the revolution on the railroad .
