The Turkish justice dismissed for the Kurdish side and this decision carries heavy consequences.
Turkish Constitutional Court on Friday decided to cancel the main pro-Kurdish party in the country. The decision immediately triggered a protest demonstration s in the Kurdish community in the south-east of the country and Istanbul.
This decision could greatly complicate the task of government , which is trying to to the Kurdish community a friendly hand to attempt to end 25 years of conflict .
For the Democratic Party (DTP), the company was disbanded because it has become a "nest of activities against the independence of the state and its indivisible unity," he told journalists, the chairman of the Supreme Court Hasim Kilic after four days of negotiations.
The decision was adopted unanimously by the 11 judges, when it was needed for the dissolution of the majority-seven votes, said Kiliç and added that 37 of party cadres, including its president Ahmeta Türka Aysely Tuglukové and the ban to participate in the political life for a period of five years.
The judge also announced the abolition of parliamentary immunity enjoyed by Mr and Mrs Türk Tugluková and confiscation of property by the Ministry of Finance.
The DTP party has 21 seats in Parliament (500).
Party leadership has indicated before the verdict that members of Parliament rather than leave it served as members of no political affiliation.
The decision is a continuation of the process launched in 2007, the chief justice of the Court of Cassation Abdurrahmanem Yalcinkayem, who accused the DTP of obedience to "commands" Party of Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK), which Ankara and many countries regard as a terrorist organization.
Many observers believe that the DTP is legal political vitrínou rebels from the PKK .
Page assures that the PKK has no "essential link", but refuses to designate a terrorist organization and calls on the government to negotiate with it.
The court's verdict comes at a time when the government gives the Kurdish community in a friendly hand and offers a range of measures to strengthen their rights and attempting to limit the support of Kurds against the PKK and end the conflict.
DTP executives confirmed that the dissolution of the parties could lead to a renewal of tensions in southeastern Anatolia, where degenerated in recent weeks, many demonstrations against the conditions under which the detained PKK leader Abdullah Öcalan in clashes with police.
From the notification of the decision of justice, thousands of protesters gathered in front of the seat of the DTP in Diyarbakiru, a big city in the southeast, which is occupied by mostly Kurds.
The police used the normalization era and water cannon, the protesters threw again Molotovovy cocktails or shooting stones from the slings.
Also in Istanbul demonstrated about a hundred people.
After delivery of the verdict, Mr. Türk said that the decision of justice "will deepen despair.
Turkey is unable to this question (Kurds to resolve the ban, he said in a press release.
The government, consisting of a party came from the Islamist movement, also condemned the decision.
We are from the principle against interference of the parties.
It does not solve anything, said Minister for Energy Taner Yildiz.
This Decision is an utter [Democratic proposals, which was initiated by the government, said political scientist Ahmet Insel.
Of course, we can wait for reaction from the PKK, he said.
On Thursday, the PKK subscribed to one of the most deadly attacks in the north of Turkey, which killed three days earlier seven soldiers.
The new Silicon-Valley
Long years was true for a city, inaccessible to visitors from the West.
Zelenograd, one of the 10 districts of the capital city of Moscow, in the Soviet Union, it was a closely guarded location, where they performed a secret weapons research.
Today, it is considered to be the district with 216 000 inhabitants, remote 37 miles from Moscow Center, "Russian Silicon Valley".
There are significant micro- and nanoelektronická research and manufacturing centre.
Since September 2008 established zelenogradští contacts with representatives of Frankfurt scientific centre Riedberg - with the university institutions and firms frankfurtského Innovation Centre (FIZ).
There has been a series of mutual visits and on Wednesday signed in Frankfurt and Zelenograd Ridberg "the Protocol on close co-operation".
The Russian delegation was led Moscow Yuri vícestarosta Rosljak and the prefect of Anatoly Zelenogradu Smirnov in Frankfurt foot the head clerk planning Edwin Schwarz.
In 2010, they'll go representatives FIZ and small and medium-sized enterprises involved in research on one seminar in Zelenogradu.
Scientific exchange
This is an ongoing scientific exchange.
But it is also about economic relations.
FIZu companies will be allowed to grip the growing Russian market.
On the contrary, the Russian scientific firms want to get a contract in Germany.
Zelenograd is the major russian research institutes and companies.
These include the need for the Moscow Institute of electronic technology, large groups and Sitronics Rossijskaja electronics.
The district was founded in 1958 as a so-called "socialist planning" for weapons research.
Zelenograd (the literal translation of the "Green City") acquired its name in the wooded hilly landscape in which they are given a research facility.
Stuttgartská brake
Dimension Stuttgart 21 simply can not adequately prepare.
For fans of the project is quite simply a "new heart of Europe".
Well. S21 is more than running the station, more than a monstrous building, which throws the capital of Baden-Württemberg for a decade building a desperate chaos.
Stuttgart 21 originated from the spirit of the 1980s.
Hlavové station with the rails, which ended in the centre of town, was then considered to be a reach-technical fossils of the 19th century, which acts as a brake modern rail transport, because it had to be enormously much time on přepřáhnutí locomotives from the back to the front.
Go, stop for a moment, go on - so it should work.
And why are disappearing hlavová station: in Frankfurt and Munich.
And in Stuttgart: the transit station, which lies roughly in the middle of the route of trans-European highway between Paris and Budapest / Bratislava - hence the slogan of "the heart of Europe".
Indeed, starting with S21, although the vision of the 80 years are no longer compatible with reality.
Ourselves very ambitious designers know that the Hessen and Bavarian metropolis is the start of construction almost neufinancovatelné.
Since there is a modern shuttle trains in motor vehicles and managing at both ends, they don't have any problems with the train station hlavová zajížděním and vyjížděním.
Still: It starts with the Stuttgart 21, with a new track ICE to Ulm.
Enforce that surface and local politicians.
Track shall cooperate, because of the risk of an individual's biggest infrastructure project in the Czech Republic will be borne by the taxpayer and no public concern.
Urban, the project is still some way to apologize.
A new urban area , which - if we are to believe the computer images - will contain many green .
For rail transport system is S21 harmful.
Transit station and the construction of the line are designed for passenger transport, which - typically in the 80 years - highlighted the huge increase.
Then there was no competition from low-cost flights.
Modern transport policy has to go but primarily for the strengthening of freight transport, because the rail transport is more environmentally friendly than the freight car on the road.
But a new line is not due to a sharp rise suitable for freight trains.
Even more important is that the S21, indirectly affects many other railway projects.
In Švábsku should bury a good six billion euros.
This is the official number.
Experts consider to be the real ten to 15 billion.
It is clear that the next decade will miss the finances for the next hub points and narrow space on the network.
On the list of the Ministry of Transport is sixty larger projects.
One of the most important is the construction of approximately 180 kilometers long route through the valley of the Rhine.
Since 1987, on this route puts the slow pace.
There would be a need for a push.
But S21 will be as a brake.
The track of the Rhine valley will become the neck of the bottle of international freight transport: Directly in the heart of Europe.
