The worlds dreams
Some see the images in the waking state and hear voices that others see and hear.
Not only the mentally ill or in the drug influence are the boundaries between imagination and reality.
Until this occurs during sleep, everything is fine.
If we lie to shut our eyes in a dark room, we may surround the wildest imagination and fantastical delusions.
But who is experiencing a dream-like states of vigilance, sees and hears things that others see and hear are at today's Western world mostly a fool or a drug dependent, or at least as eccentric.
But such images and voices are due not only for the mentally ill or in the drug intoxication.
Guilt is our imagination: The same neural processes that allow us to design houses, paint pictures or write novels, here and there to take care of that blend the boundaries between dream, vision and reality.
The dreams of the altered state of consciousness may be present in various forms, at best, we call them a vision in the worst delusions.
Even if the initiator and effect may vary, however, vision mystičky Hildegard von Bingen, drug experiences of the Prophet New-Age Carlos Castanedy, estimated that states of delirium, psychoses and hallucinations derived from similar processes.
Delusions or hallucinations arise when the derailment balance neuronálních transmitérů - especially the brain's dopamine, noradrenalin (norepinephrine, serotonin and acetylcholine - and the interaction between the different parts of the brain is disturbed.
A comprehensive hallucinations and wandering thoughts occur very often in the schizophrenic psychosis .
Gravity above it does not have the power
The link between dreams and delusions of employed doctors and philosophers since antiquity.
Aristotle understood as a form of hallucination, a dream in the waking state, Wilhelm Griesinger, one of the founders of modern psychology, said in 1861 "the great similarity ravings with dream states, the Sigmund Freud was a dream even" psychosis, with all the nonsense, delusion, deception of the senses " .
It is the autumn of 2001, Henning T. is amended in comic figure.
His body is a two-dimensional, and brightly colored.
Gravity above it has no power, hovering near the ceiling of the room.
Feels the kick.
Behind him the winged spirited figures with blood red grimace, cenící teeth.
Chasing him, kick him in the heavy, fiery shoes, throwing him on the wall, feel the pain throughout the body.
Loud, evil voices from the walls and threaten the radio.
We can not tolerate voices that curse and insult him.
Henning T. pulls two cables from the stereo, zauzlí it into a loop and fastened it on a hook on the ceiling.
Stand up to one speaker and you can loop around the neck.
Jumping.
Loop permits.
Learn, a chorus of voices shouting trhajíc his eardrums, "go to the clinic and get help!"
Today's Henning T. 40 years, has seen six acute psychoses, the last two years ago, the first for nearly 20 years ago.
They were running LSD.
His diagnosis is schizoafektivní paranoická psychosis, moreover, there is a manic-depressive, he takes medication for depression, mania, schizophrenia.
He learned to live with their disease, three years is married.
In a psychosis, I experienced the worst fear and deep doubts, he says.
The ghosts are a terrible reality
About one percent of people get sick at least once in a lifetime schizophrenia in psychiatric clinics is the second most commonly depression treatment of disease.
An acute schizophrenic psychosis can usually distinguish between the inner and outer world into přebuzeného condition, which can lead to weeks, velikostním, vztahovým delusions or delusions of persecution.
Especially widespread is hearing voices - voices that Command, comment or maintain dialogue.
Neither optical hallucinations are not uncommon.
The person is not able to distinguish between the important from the unimportant, the brain can filter spurious signals, consciousness is flooded with impressions.
Just as the dream of psychosis opens the floodgates of a barrage of ideas and fantasies that originate from the deepest layers of consciousness.
The perception of reality in psychosis is centered on the body, says Professor Thomas Fuchs, chief surgeon general psychiatric Clinic the university clinic in Heidelberg.
A schizophrenic is located in the centre of the stage, it is important směřovaný at him.
At the same time, it is a passive role, becoming, like a dream, overwhelmed by events and cannot is actively shape.
Schizophrenia is therefore often feel threatened, manipulated and controlled.
Comparison with reality is not usually possible for them, they are a terrible reality, awakening is out of the question.
Once in a lifetime experience hallucination
Otherwise than in a dream, says Fuchss, "but still sensual and spatial structure of the fact that one sees in psychosis, substantially preserved."
The erratic thoughts and hallucinations are based on the reality of the experience is occurring in the real framework.
Scientists is still the puzzle as to why our brain is doing exactly the sort of twists.
The exceptional conditions for each person can lead to lose in the short-term relationship to reality, says Fuchs.
Not everyone, however, develop into a psychosis.
It seems that there is a genetic disposition to schizophrenia, but the twin studies have shown that genes are not the only determining factor.
Scientists are based on the fact that disabled people have a minimum damage to the brain .
We believe that in the early stage of development will damage the neuronal maturation of the brain, such as viral diseases of the mother during pregnancy, says Fuchs.
But it remains a puzzle, as there is a failure of neuronal systems, which in doing so for years does not materialize.
The role of the effects of the neighborhood - stress or traumatic experiences can be instigated psychosis, if it is to her disposition.
Also the hallucinogenic drugs can trigger psychosis, because the transmission system.
When our brain tube
Crazy is that psychotronici suffers from their hallucinations, and to get rid of them, swallowed expensive medication, others give you money for drugs to be gained, says psychology professor Erich Kasten of Lübeck.
If the images we perceive as pleasant or unpleasant, it is often just a matter of attitude.
Kasten collector for ten years, reports of hallucinations and delusions, in the last year interpreted their results in the book "Die Welt irreale in unserem Kopf" (unreal world in our head).
Hallucinations belongs to a typical accompanying phenomena psychóz, but also to the surprisingly many other diseases.
In addition to the psychiatric disorders such as a borderline personality or depression also often diseases like a migraine, epilepsy, multiple sclerosis or Alzheimer or brain trauma.
Surprisingly halucinuje under certain conditions, and by a healthy person's brain.
Hallucinations, according to Kasten, is composed of the contents of the ideas that are normally suppressed.
They arise when the part of the brain, which processes sensory perception, are too active or little repressed; if our brains tube, or when there is a lack of stimulation.
Drugs can run this state as well as brain damage or psychosis.
But also the withdrawal of incentives, stress, worry about love or other more exceptional States.
In the most recent studies had reported up to one-third of those surveyed reported at least once in your life experienced an hallucination.
In the summer of 2005 is Sarah K. 16 years old, lives in a small town in eastern Pomerania Meklenbursku-front and goes to the grammar school.
In fact, a normal girl.
If there were not the shapes and voices.
At recess, it may be that appeals to her bony with long, dark hair.
When he replies, looking at her classmates with a surprise - no one except her see and hear the boy.
This coy girl as stiff a dreamer, but Sarah K.-eater, knows it.
Is awake, hears and sees the boy, exactly as they hear and see the girl sitting next to each bench.
May even feel his presence, at least for a few moments.
It's a nice feeling, he has the boy like.
I'm crazy?, asks ever.
But he knows that this boy and other delusions are not real and disappears.
In the night are rather depressing .
They are often delusions burden.
Sitting in class, can not how many times monitor teaching, because the teacher in her eyes and ears just represents a new classmate, but he explains all other audibly, and visible on the board of the mathematical equation.
In the night of phenomena rather depressing.
While waiting in his dark room to sleep, which comes rarely and too late, often can not distinguish whether it is awake or if she was asleep, if the images he sees, grimacing, or cutting a girl with bleeding wounds on the hands and feet resulting from her open or eyes closed.
Leave me alone, shouting at the figures.
Parents and friends say anything about it, thought it about her that was crazy.
The autumn of 2009. Sarah K. is now 20 years old.
Last year did high school graduation and lives with her boyfriend.
A year ago, hallucinations stopped.
Since she contacted on the internet psychologist Kasten, knows exactly that went mad.
The images are also the art of despair
If someone is socially isolated or had taken incentives will likely hallucinations, says Kasten.
I believe that the brain then doesn't have enough employment and old himself for his own amusement .
Sarah K., an only child, she was a little girl fear of the other children, often played by herself.
Her hallucinations began when, at 13, she learned that the man who says he since she thinks is her own father.
Because the visual and acoustic hallucinations are active the same brain areas that process the real sensations and sounds, for people like Sarah K. difficult to distinguish from one another delusion and reality. "Every experience," says Kasten, "takes place in the brain, the reality shows there.
Hallucinations are also images that allow the brain occur, so the real work."
Also the dreams evaluates Kasten as a form of hallucinations.
Hallucinations healthy people does not differ fundamentally from hallucinations in acute psychosis.
Unlike schizofrenikům are mentally healthy people will be able to identify their delusions as unrealistic.
Kasten therefore advise their patients to evaluate the hallucinations as an extraordinary ability.
Border state between dreams and hallucinations
In our world, concentrated too much on the minds is an imaginary experience, unfortunately, the majority patologizován, says Michael Schmidt-Degenhard, a professor in Heidelberg and the Chief Medical Officer psychotherapy and Psychiatric Clinic Hospital-Florence Nightingale in Düsseldorf.
Psychosis is difficult, útrpná disease, but it also provides the positives, creativity - a mirage is also art of despair.
The so-called Schmidt-Degenhard oneiroidní form of experiences, a special form of changed the consciousness of the dream.
Oneiroidní states are highly complex, detailed fictional dreams, which is considered to be the real and can't even re-distinguished from waking.
Oneiroidní state of consciousness arises in extreme situations caused by trauma or illness, such as hepatitis polyradikulárním patients who experience fully conscious motor paralysis.
If a person is threatened by the loss of the world and themselves, to be continued, the complete inability of movement, will be replaced with a life-threatening the real situation of their own, imagined a world that is disconnected from reality, says Schmidt-Degenhard.
The type of the state between dreams and hallucinations.
Because in reality it is not possible to deal with any situation, there is a change of worlds, the real situation but zpřítomní the idea.
Intensive form of aid senses and the transfer of the senses in an intolerable situation, which allows people to his own ability to shape, change in an instant by a loss of consciousness.
Everything is real, and later in the memories
Also, the art historian Peter Cornelius Claussen oneiroidní describes his experiences in his book "Herzwechsel" (Replacement Heart) as a rescue of the soul.
He was 49 years old when, after the operation with subsequent heart valves of the heart transplant was his awareness for several days of travel, with his body lay motionless in intensive care.
Claussen sank into a world that had formed, visited foreign time and place: the old man upoutaným on the bed, in the train the sanatorium, the robot guarding his health.
He lives in the early Middle Ages among the aristocracy, which manufactures narcotic substances in the blood.
Greek kidnaps him on the bike to his homeland, in a hospital bed in the Alps or surfing on firnu meets the Korean mobster.
Completely immersed in an imaginary wrong, everything is fair, and later in memory.
These internal path for Claussena fundamentally different from any dream.
The dream is a different situation, describes his experience.
In contrast to the dreams are memories of the mental pathways across the years and about minor details plainly obvious.
Even clearer and more intense than the actual experience.
The intensity of this experience shatters the horizon of our other opravdivých experience, says psychiatrist Schmidt-Degenhard.
After all, show oneiroidní anxiety, psychosis, hallucinations and drug intoxication, how fragile are also waking up our internal images of external reality.
Any change in the state of consciousness, summarises the psychologist Kasten, "can lead to distortion of what we call reality."
The fact that may also be enriching.
