Promise FonPeek
Peak is extremely limited, serve only to explore the mail, without the ability to view a type of attachments or surfing in the network.
Enjoyed his five minutes of fame in the U.S., when Time magazine praised it as one of the products of the year.
It is difficult to see out there, but the idea may be interesting, especially for young people.
Unlike smartphonů Peak is characterised by a very low price and monthly payments, less than half the amount payable for example, for a data plan for the iPhone.
After his success, the company has started offering two new devices: One is intended exclusively for Twitter, second on the basis of permanently provided free data service, for which it is necessary to pay for the Peak six changes amount.
FonPeek, which was presented yesterday to try Le Web, is a European version of invention, and at the same time, his third transformation.
Is limited, as well as his american counterpart, but it brings a surprise.
The monthly price for maintenance is around 12 euros per month and includes the roaming across Europe.
People travelling with smartphonem already know what it means to lose data services after crossing the border or impatiently seek café with WiFi (or inserting Fon), so they can view the mail.
The idea of having roomingem at a fixed price is incredibly attractive and should be put in place for a long time.
Yes, some operators have specific contracts and travel plans, but in my experience, one would need a doctorate in physics, in order to understand them, and very good glasses to read the miniature letters.
The European Commission has sought to reduce roaming tariffs so that they are available for the whole of Europe, which still does not have the desired effect.
There is a reasonable concern on the use of data services outside the home .
The fact that such a machine like FonPeek (interestingly, still has the name Fon when there is no WiFi) reaches this type of fare, means that the operators are starting to think otherwise, and is considering various offers kterýmiby kompenzovali its data network.
Kindle is another nice example, offers downloads of books and other searches on the Internet.
No contract, no complications.
This device is connected and paid for the purchase, rather than months.
And that is exactly what I expect to occur once in případěFonPeek, it is a possibility to book with permanent access as the Peak has already established in the US.
Not because I wanted to buy it.
I am looking through the mail, on the phone, thank you.
