75% of working mothers to work problems associated with maternity.
Discrimination in employment in recent years has increased, especially in younger women who intend to buy a child.
That is the result of the study and the career of Spanish , which is carried out in cooperation with the Institute of Women .
The study was attended by 9.737 women aged from 15 to 75 years, and the results are clear: 75% of working mothers have limited options in the labour market because of motherhood.
The study points out that at the beginning of the partner coexistence is the many differences of opinion on the number of children, depending on whether they work or not, as well as to the type of employment.
Women, who do not work outside the home, working part-time or have a stable job, starting with a partner to live before, previously gave birth to their first child and generally have more children.
From the other side, women with stable employment, especially in the public sector partner cohabitation and motherhood delay, and have fewer offspring.
"Women from 35 to 49 years with stable jobs have their first child at an average of 3.7 years from the start of living with a partner. The number of 4.1 in the case of the women kterédosažení its stable jobs are dedicated to the greater part of his life, and thus have had to postpone the partner relationship, and the arrival of children.
The type of the profession has also had a strong influence on maternity, even if a smaller effect on the duration of living with a partner, "explains margaritas Delgado, devoted to the research in the CSIC.
Another factor affecting the age of women at the time of the marriage of a child is the level of education .
Research indicates that the higher the level of education, the higher is the age when women marry and have their first child.
Differences are also among the women of the same generation.
For example, in the age group of 35 to 49 years of women with the basic and higher education given birth to their first child at the age of 25.1 or 32.1.
"There is another difference between women depending on their level of education.
Women with basic schooling to marry and gave birth to their first child before they find a stable job, while women with a medium or high education ’ s reverse prefer to obtain a stable employment, before the conclusion of a marriage and the birth of the first child, "says Delgado.
