The system for the handbrake is already mandatory equipment.
As in the case of antiblokovacího ABS system, it will be with the ESP stability control, auxiliary systems of the handbrake, it all becomes mandatory equipment of European cars.
In fact, already form part of the required equipment all newly registered passenger cars and light commercial vehicles, while the other is determined by the deadline for the removal of the shortage, which it is February 2011.
The measures introduced in the EU aims to enhance the protection of pedestrians, the works so that it can help to avoid the many collisions.
Auxiliary hand brake system increases the pressure on the brakes in an emergency, this system detects when the driver presses.
But not always able to keep the pressure until the end.
According to a study carried out by an automotive parts manufacturer Bosch, a third of drivers who have an accident, nesešlápli brake before the collision, and half of them did not use the full power of the brakes.
Up to 1,100 accidents
On the contrary, this assistance requires maximum braking systems, reducing the stopping distance of the vehicle.
According to a study conducted by the EU itself, if all vehicles were equipped with this type of device, it could prevent up to 1 in 100 fatalities per year related to pedestrians.
A reduction in this rate will be even more marked-based on calculations would avoid one of the four casualties with an impact on a person-following the introduction of the so-called intelligent systems of the handbrake.
In this case, the vehicle is fitted with a system that (using radar and cameras) captures the obstacles and reports them to the driver, except for the light braking.
If the driver responds, it will help to increase the pressure on the pedal if necessary.
If the driver does not react, even in the event of a collision cannot be avoided, the device will act as a brake on a nejintenzivněji and reduce the risk of damage to a minimum.
