If, as we expect, we find ourselves before the standardisation of premiums from the transitional risk, after some excesech on assisted positions would have been within expectations.
In the Spanish case, while our differences in the public debt will rise, as well as bonds of European companies, we don't have to worry about.
If the European differences will be reduced, and our continued to expand, it would be a typical Spanish risk.
