After his intervention, after which was followed by the resignation of the president of the Natural Gas-Fenosa, Rafael Villasecy, Galán gave the press a few comments on the proposal, presented by podkomisi behind closed doors.
According to the president of Iberdrola, Spain needs investment 50,000 million by 2020, and other 60.000 million from that date by 2030, if we are to retain the nuclear plants, which are currently in operation.
If not, the necessary investment will not be 60.000 million but to 95.000 million.
Iberdrola really believes that in the next decade, the investment must focus not on increasing production capacity, but the distribution network and international links
By 2020, the question of changing, and it will be necessary to increase performance.
Its menu focuses on the ballot and coal-fired power station with carbon dioxide capture mechanisms and largely on renewable energy.
In this case, believes that there is a need for new 18.000 MW, but with other "supporting energy".
Galán, who believes ženávrh law on a sustainable economy, which was approved by the government, the line that the company requested wouldn't air bleed like the Royal Decree to promote the consumption of coal, which is contrary to the policy of combating climate change.
