The FCC has been assigned a tunnel in Slovenia for 64 million
The FCC, through its affiliates Alpine received the award of the construction of the tunnel with a length of 2.1 miles of the highway in Slovenia in value as 64.5 million.
The firm received a contract for a few days after the completion of the work on the extension of the tunnel in Bosrucku (Austria) for 130 million.
In this way, Alpine strengthens its experience in the construction of the tunnels.
The work is scheduled for the beginning of 2010, and the deadline for transposition is 32 months.
