Fine 63 million proFrance Télécom for braking competition
The regulatory authority for the competition in France, impose a fine of EUR 63 million lFrance Télécom in anti-competitive behaviour in the Caribbean areas, which belongs to the ground.
According to this institution operator limited competition in the fixed and mobile phones signing exclusive agreements, pricing plans and programmes of loyalty with consumers on the edge of the regulation.
The sanctions , the former French monopoly and state the company piled up more than 560 million euro fines since 1994 for the laying of the obstacles to its competitors .
The fine imposed yesterday was de facto increased because the office that oversees the competition, believes that France Telecom has committed a similar offense as in the past, and that therefore there was a relapse.
Trade with applications
On the other hand, a mobile branch of the French company is still a star among other operators and opened trade with applications on the Internet to increase revenue that will come from voice transmissions.
From the beginning, it will be a deal with applications Orange active in France and Great Britain.
You will have to wait until 2010 at the entrance to other countries, such as Spain.
